{"lemma":"عَقِّي","slug":"عَقِّي","root":"ع.ق.ق","root_slug":"ع-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30027","n30029"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%91%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split, to cleave","examples":[{"text":"يَعُقُّ الْكُرْدُوسُ بَيْنَ الْمُشَاشَةِ وَجِسْمِ الْعَظْمِ","english":"The metaphysis separates the epiphysis and the diaphysis."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become disobedient, disrespectful to"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕaq.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30027","headword_ar":"عقّى","root":"EqY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose high in his flight."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~ati Ald~alowu","text_ar":"عَقَّتِ الدَّلْوُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bucket rose"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the well"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning round."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqw","text_ar":"عقو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also 1, (last sentence,) in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq","text_ar":"عق"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~Y","text_ar":"عقّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisahomihi","text_ar":"بِسَهْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoqiyapN","text_ar":"تَعْقِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shot his arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"up"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the air;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~ahu","text_ar":"عَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~a bihi","text_ar":"عَقَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) The Hudhalee, (S,) El-Mutanakhkhil, (TA,) or Aboo-Dhu-eyb, (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wDH","text_ar":"وضح"},{"kind":"text","text":",) says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Eaq~awoA bisahomK falmo ya$oEuro bihi A^aHadN\n                      \n                     \n                        vum~a A@sotafaAw^uwA waqaAluwA Hab~a*aA AlwaDaHu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They shot an arrow towards the sky, and no one knew of it: then they returned, and said, An excellent thing is milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) meaning, “ we would rather have milk than the blood of him who killed our companion; ” preferring that camels should be given them as a compensation: (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wDH","text_ar":"وضح"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is related [thus] with fet-h to the doubled"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that its place is here; and also with damm thereto, so that its place is art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq","text_ar":"عق"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which it has been mentioned. (TA. [See a similar verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~a","text_ar":"عَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the explanation thereof, there preceding that verse.])       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~Ahu","text_ar":"عقّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him to drink"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to swallow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what would cause his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqoY","text_ar":"عِقْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to pass forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honey in order that it might have that effect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30029","headword_ar":"عِقْىٌ","root":"EqY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What comes forth from the belly of the child"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before he eats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when he is born,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black and viscous as though it were glue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the mare's foal, and the young ass, and the young camel, and the kid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA;) or what comes forth from the lamb or kid, and the mare's foal, is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radajN","text_ar":"رَدَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and Az states that it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what comes forth from the belly of the fœtus, inclosed in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"membrane called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwalaA='","text_ar":"حُوَلَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that comes forth from its anus while it is in the belly of its mother, part of it black and part of it yellow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaA='N","text_ar":"اَعْقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraSu mino kalobK EalaY EiqoYi SabiY~K","text_ar":"اَحْرَصُ مِنْ كَلْبٍ عَلَى عِقْىِ صَبِىٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a prov. [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More eager than a dog for the feces of a young child"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A youngling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young infant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the saying of Z, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN lahu EiqoyaAni walayosa Einodahu AlEiqoyaAnu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَهُ عِقْيَانِ وَلَيْسَ عِنْدَهُ العِقْيَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has two younglings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young infants, but gold is not in his possession."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}